    "recap_headline": "College of Charleston",
    "recap_text": "MT PLEASANT, S.C. \u2013\nCollege of Charleston baseball lost to No. 19 Clemson, 3-1, Tuesday evening at Patriots Point.\nRedshirt senior\nAlex Lyon\nthrew four shutout innings of relief for Charleston (9-11), going three above the minimum. All three of Clemson's (17-4) runs came from Nate Savoie, who hit a pair of homers.\nCRITICAL POINTS AGAINST CLEMSON:\nTwo batters into the game, Savoie hit his first home run to give the Tigers an early 1-0 advantage.\nSavoie made it a 3-0 ballgame with a two-run shot in the top of the third.\nCharleston responded in the home half when redshirt freshman\nWill Burgess\ntripled in freshman\nStow Rogers\n.\nFreshman\nJake Amman\nhit the game's second three-bagger with a two-out triple in the fifth.\nFreshman\nKaden Myers\ntossed the eighth and ninth innings, yielding a lone hit.\nOF NOTE:\nTuesday's crowd of 1,680 set a Patriots Point single game attendance record.\nCharleston is 5-27 in the series with Clemson.\nLyon made his 86th career relief appearance, taking sole possession of second in school history in the category.\nLyon has gone at least 4.0 innings for the third time this season and seventh time in his career.\nGraduate\nDylan Johnson\nthrew out his 40th career would-be base stealer, tying him with Alex Garabedian (2006-07) for the second-most in school history.\nJohnson extended hit on base streak to 11 games with a single in the fourth.\nThe Cougars hit two triples in a game for the first time since May 4, 2024, at Towson.\nUP NEXT:\nCharleston welcomes CAA rival UNCW to Patriots Point for a three-game series March 20-22. First pitch in the opener is set for 6 p.m.\nStanding room only tickets available for purchase by visiting\ncofcsports./tickets\nor by calling the Ticket Office at (843) 953-2632.\nFor complete coverage of Charleston baseball, follow us X (@CofCBaseball) and Instagram (@CofC_Baseball)."
  },
